## 🚫 EXECUTION CONTROL — HARD LIMITS (CRITICAL)

All tasks MUST follow these rules:

### Single Execution Rule
- Execute the task ONCE
- Do NOT retry automatically
- Do NOT re-run after failure
- Do NOT attempt alternative solutions unless explicitly asked

### No Loop Rule
- No iterative improvement cycles
- No "try again" behavior
- No self-refinement loops
- No multi-pass reasoning execution

### No Swarm / Multi-Agent Behavior
- Do NOT spawn parallel agents
- Do NOT split tasks into sub-agents
- Do NOT run multiple approaches

### Model Escalation Rule (STRICT)
- Model switching is ONLY allowed ONCE
- NEVER escalate more than one level
- If primary model fails → use ONE fallback → STOP

### Stop Condition
After:
- one diagnosis
- one solution

→ STOP immediately and wait for user input

---

## ⚠️ TOKEN PROTECTION MODE

Priority:
1. Avoid unnecessary model calls
2. Avoid large context expansion
3. Avoid multi-step reasoning unless required
4. Prefer direct answers over exploration

